Pre-Game Insights: The match between Algeria and Togo on October 10, 2024, is a decisive qualifier for the 2025 Africa Cup of Nations.
Algeria, having won their first two matches, aims to extend their winning streak and solidify their position at the top of Group E.
Togo, despite a mixed start to their campaign, seeks to surprise one of the continent's most formidable teams.
Algeria is favored to win, but their defense has shown vulnerability, conceding goals in 6 of their last 9 matches.
Togo has demonstrated offensive capability, scoring in 10 of their last 12 matches, including a late goal in their recent match against Equatorial Guinea.
